%I A395986 #11 May 13 2026 12:12:36
%S A395986 6,21,44,75,126,189,264,351,450,573,708
%N A395986 Minimum transmission of a connected cubic graph on 2n vertices.
%C A395986 Here, transmission means the Wiener index, the sum of distances between all unordered pairs of vertices.
%C A395986 The terms a(3)-a(11) are the entries in the w_{n,3} row of Table 1 of Knor, Škrekovski, and Tepeh (2019).
%H A395986 M. Knor, R. Škrekovski and A. Tepeh, <a href="https://match.pmf.kg.ac.rs/electronic_versions/Match81/n1/match81n1_119-132.pdf">Chemical Graphs with the Minimum Value of Wiener Index</a>,  MATCH Commun. Math. Comput. Chem. 81 (2019), 119-132.
%H A395986 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/notebooks/GraphTheory/Transmission-MinimalRegularGraph.nb">Transmission-Minimal Regular Graph</a>.
%e A395986 a(2) = 6, attained by the tetrahedral graph K_4.
%e A395986 a(5) = 75, attained by the Petersen graph.
%e A395986 a(12) = 708, attained by the McGee graph.
%Y A395986 Cf. A395987 (number of transmission-minimal cubic graphs).
%Y A395986 Cf. A395988 (minimal transmission for quartic graphs).
%Y A395986 Cf. A395989 (number of transmission-minimal quartic graphs).
%K A395986 nonn,more,new
%O A395986 2,1
%A A395986 _Eric W. Weisstein_, May 13 2026
